docs.abstract: Ms. Warren’s passion for policy minutiae has become her way of distinguishing herself in a large Democratic field. But some voters say she risks being seen as out of touch and too intellectual.
docs.snippet: Ms. Warren’s passion for policy minutiae has become her way of distinguishing herself in a large Democratic field. But some voters say she risks being seen as out of touch and too intellectual.
docs.lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — The gym was hot. The lights malfunctioned. But the audience of nearly 1,000 people was engrossed as Senator Elizabeth Warren, the Massachusetts Democrat and presidential hopeful, did what she does best: “nerd out,” as she puts it.

headline.main: Elizabeth Warren’s 2020 Strategy: Stand Out by ‘Nerding Out’
headline.print_headline: Warren Hopes Voters Are Up For Nerdy Talk

docs.abstract: Ms. Harris, a Democratic senator from California, described the nation and the world as at “an inflection point” in history. “Who are we as Americans?” she asked at the rally on Sunday.
docs.snippet: Ms. Harris, a Democratic senator from California, described the nation and the world as at “an inflection point” in history. “Who are we as Americans?” she asked at the rally on Sunday.
docs.lead_paragraph: OAKLAND, Calif. — Senator Kamala Harris of California officially kicked off her campaign for the Democratic presidential nomination on Sunday at an outdoor rally where she warned that the nation and the world were at “an inflection point” in history and called on all Americans to “speak truth about what’s happening” in the Trump era.

headline.main: Kamala Harris Kicks Off 2020 Campaign With Oakland Rally
headline.print_headline: Large Rally In California Starts Race For Harris

docs.abstract: Mr. O’Rourke, considering a run for president, took to the road to find answers. And he wrote quite a bit about it.
docs.snippet: Mr. O’Rourke, considering a run for president, took to the road to find answers. And he wrote quite a bit about it.
docs.lead_paragraph: Beto O’Rourke does not know whether he wants to run for president. He does know where he thinks he’ll find the answer: behind the wheel. In a series of posts on Medium, Mr. O’Rourke has detailed his somewhat aimless recent travels — seeing sights, thinking thoughts, dining with strangers — in a confessional style uncommon among presidential contenders.

headline.main: Beto O’Rourke On the Road: An Annotated Travel Log

docs.abstract: After she delivered the Democratic response to the State of the Union address, some admirers asked why the clamoring has been louder for some white men to run than for her.
docs.snippet: After she delivered the Democratic response to the State of the Union address, some admirers asked why the clamoring has been louder for some white men to run than for her.
docs.lead_paragraph: Seconds into the Democratic response to President Trump’s State of the Union address Tuesday evening, speculation took off about the political future of Stacey Abrams, the Georgia leader who was delivering the remarks on behalf of her party.

headline.main: Stacey Abrams Isn’t Running for President. Should She Be?
headline.print_headline: Supporters Nudge Democrat With High Aspirations to Aim Even Higher

docs.abstract: Mr. Bennet, a moderate Democrat from Colorado, has been involved in bipartisan Senate compromises on immigration, education and other issues.
docs.snippet: Mr. Bennet, a moderate Democrat from Colorado, has been involved in bipartisan Senate compromises on immigration, education and other issues.
docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Michael Bennet of Colorado, the 21st Democrat to declare his candidacy for president, is known as a moderate who seeks bipartisan compromise. Here’s where he stands on a few key issues.

headline.main: Where Michael Bennet Stands on the Issues

docs.abstract: Right-wing commentators accused the president of folding on a central promise and predicted that it would hurt him among voters who have long stood by him.
docs.snippet: Right-wing commentators accused the president of folding on a central promise and predicted that it would hurt him among voters who have long stood by him.
docs.lead_paragraph: Some of the most prominent voices in the conservative base were furious at President Trump on Friday after he agreed to reopen the government without getting money for a border wall — the sort of terms he had spent more than a month rejecting. They derided the deal as a capitulation by a leader who they had trusted to stand firm.

headline.main: Did Trump Cave on the Wall? Some Conservatives Say Yes

docs.abstract: Mr. Buttigieg has formed an exploratory committee for a run for the White House in 2020, joining an expanding Democratic field.
docs.snippet: Mr. Buttigieg has formed an exploratory committee for a run for the White House in 2020, joining an expanding Democratic field.
docs.lead_paragraph: Pete Buttigieg, the 37-year-old mayor of South Bend, Ind., announced on Wednesday that he was entering the Democratic presidential primary, embarking on a long-shot campaign that may test the appeal of a youthful, Midwestern profile over more traditional qualifications for the presidency.

headline.main: Pete Buttigieg, Mayor of South Bend, Ind., Joins Democratic 2020 Race
headline.print_headline: Young Mayor From Indiana Latest to Seek White House

docs.abstract: Ms. McGrath won without the backing of national Democrats. A viral video about her military experience helped generate more than $1 million in donations.
docs.snippet: Ms. McGrath won without the backing of national Democrats. A viral video about her military experience helped generate more than $1 million in donations.
docs.lead_paragraph: RICHMOND, Ky. — Amy McGrath, who packaged her biography as the first female Marine to fly in an F-18 fighter jet in combat with a powerful anti-Washington message, won the Democratic House primary in Kentucky’s Sixth congressional district Tuesday, according to The Associated Press.

headline.main: Amy McGrath, Once a Fighter Pilot, Wins Democratic Primary for Kentucky’s 6th District

docs.lead_paragraph: NEWTOWN, Conn. — Six years ago this month, Mark Barden and Nicole Hockley watched from the gallery, counting the yeas, as the Senate voted on expanding background checks.

headline.main: Newtown Wasn’t an End for Gun Control. It Was a Beginning.
headline.print_headline: Defeat in 2013 Gave  Gun-Control Activists A Base to Work From
